Add four spheres:

center (0, 1, -3) radius 1   object_color = (1.0, 0.5, 0.5)

center (2, 1, -4) radius 1    object_color = (0.5, 1.0, 0.5)

center (-2, 1, -3) radius 1    object_color = (0.5, 0.5, 1.0)

center (0, -100, 0) radius 100    object_color = (1.0, 1.0, 1.0)


 
Same background color as last assignment

Shading: color is object_color*max(0.0, normal_vector_y)

Shadow: if ray from hitpoint in direction (0, 1, 0) hits anything change color to (0,0,0)